br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1911.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Disarm</span><hr size=1> Emphasis on the ANY mob bit- doesn't even have to be blue, a level 1 greenie works just fine.  Why to do it aside from PVP is the question, since it's relatively useless otherwise...<br><br>RdT. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubludar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bludar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/12/02 4:30:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1911.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Disarm</span><hr size=1> I have never gotten a skill raise on a mob that did not have a weapon in its hand and I use it every time it refreshes to help with aggro.  So I do not believe you can get raises on mobs with no weapons.  Some mobs do not look like they have weapons, but if you watch messages you may see you were slashed or pierced from mobs where you see no weapon, but it is there.  On those I believe you can get raises.<br><br>The good news is that you can get skill increases on green conning mobs holding weapons.  You can find orc_pawn_01 with a rusty weapon, disarm til you succeed, kill it, and hand it to orc_pawn_02 before you start over.<br><br>Friedrick - 57th Myrmidom on Tunare server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubumbleroot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bumbleroot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/12/02 6:03:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1911.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Disarm</span><hr size=1> You can use disarm to level up against any level mob. You can not raise your skill on a mob unless it actually has a weapon in its posession.<br>Just a quick trick to raising skill. I use my number pad to correlate with my hot keys. Place taunt in one and kick in two and place disarm in ten. For hot button two and button ten make them both the same number on your keypad or however you wish to set up your hot keys. This way every time you kick you can also disarm at the same time. I have almost maxed my skill this way.<br>Another easy way to max skill is to go to the zombies and skellies at the ruins in East Commons. Make sure u dont have riposte on or you will kill the poor suckers and just keep disarming till your hearts content- you should see your skill go up every two or three mobs. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uthulikore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thulikore</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/12/02 7:46:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1911.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Disarm</span><hr size=1> I've been using Disarm religiously since it became available. I'm still not entirely sure whether or not it truly assists in agro generation, however I have never ever gotten a skillup on a mob not wielding a weapon. My Disarm skill is in the 160ish range now. Given that I think it's safe to say that a mob *must* be wielding a weapon in order for you to increase your skill.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/udaleb123.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daleb123</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/12/02 7:55:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1911.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Disarm</span><hr size=1> Sorry guys, I've gotten dozens of skill increases from unarmed MObs. It works fine, or at least it used to. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usayjinbrewster.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sayjin Brewster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 95<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/12/02 9:06:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1911.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://sayjinbrewster.homestead.com/files/tso-icon.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Disarm</span><hr size=1> it works against mobs without weapons, just try spiders after you ding.  Also, it assists in taunt, even one point, any extra agro for clicking a button that doesnt effect other skills is worth it.  Just go to a mob with no weapon or even with one, click disarm, and you'll get attacked.  (if you were in range to disarm <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=9445"><img src="http://sayjinbrewster.homestead.com/files/sb.gif"></a></center><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcol